description:
&lt;p&gt;The Children’s Directorate has an exciting opportunity for a dynamic and motivated person to join the Paediatric Endocrine and Diabetes Service to work within the Children and Young people’s Diabetes Team. The post holder will be able to:&lt;br /&gt;• work within a MDT to support children and young people with Diabetes who require education and support within the acute hospital and a range of community settings&lt;br /&gt;• support the Childrens Diabetes team to teach and assess parents and carers and cascade teaching to other health/education professionals&lt;br /&gt;• support and assist in service improvement and development&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a dynamic and innovative Children’s Nurse who has experience working particularly with children who have Diabetes, and their families. The individual will have excellent communication skills and leadership qualities. It essential that they have a full driving license and own vehicle that they can use for work purposes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Full time 37 hours 30 minutes/week&lt;/p&gt;
